Class Array<T>

Parent class

shadow:standard@Object

Interfaces

shadow:standard@CanIndex<long,T>, shadow:standard@CanIndexStore<long,T>, shadow:standard@CanIterate<T>

abstract locked class Array<T>

Class Array<T> is used to house methods for array objects. The use of Array<T> is handled by the compiler. Users should avoid using the Array<T> type explicitly.

public readonly native locked subarray(long start, long end) => (Array<T>)

Copy a subarray from the given array, starting at start and going up to but not including index end. The resulting array will require an explicit cast in order to be stored back into a normal array reference.

Parameters

start - starting index of subarray

end - index after last index in subarray

Returns

Array<T> object containing the subarray
